@(69-76=c4061.A.69) …… in the silent streets. …… bathes

$ (2 lines fragmentary)
They come out from ……; it is they who appoint the @fsux{en} priestess in the @fsux{ŋipar}, who choose the @fsux{nin-diŋir} priestess by extispicy, who establish the @fsux{gudug} priest with his curly hair.

@(77-90=c4061.A.77) On this very day, as evening approaches, the first of the seven is a fox with a sweeping tail. The second snuffles around like a dog. The third pecks greedily at caterpillars like a raven. The fourth overpowers everything like an enormous carrion-eating eagle. The fifth, although not a wolf, will fall upon a black lamb. The sixth screeches like a hawk, when he sits ……. The seventh ……, a shark in the waves. These seven are neither female deities nor male. They hinder a man and hamper a woman; they put aside (?) the woman's weapon. They spread 
{a stench
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} lamentation
}  in the Land, precisely implementing the divine powers of the gods. @wDN{Ḫendursaŋa}, you have great divine powers, more than anyone could require.


@(91-105=c4061.A.91) So that everywhere …… and holy places will be established, and so that @wDN{Gibil} the pure @noteref{i.e. fire} will be available before the @wTN{E-kur}, Lady @wDN{Ninmug} stands by at your behest. So that the holy orchards (?) will be opened up, 
{@wDN{Ama-abzu-E-kura}
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} @wDN{Dumuzid-abzu}
}  stands by at your behest. So that the bolts of holy houses will be opened, 
{@wDN{Ninniŋbunara}
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} @wDN{Ninŋarŋarŋar} (?)
}  stands by at your behest. So that there will be joy in @wSN{Umma}, @wDN{Ninbi-šu-kale} stands by at your behest. So that @wSN{Aratta} will be overwhelmed (?), @wDN{Lugalbanda} stands by at your behest. So that @wSN{Niŋin} will rise above the waters like a mountain, the minister …… stands by at your behest. So that ……, …… stands by at your behest.
